The paper deals with the problem of recovering the cost function of a robot manipulator from incomplete observations of its optimal trajectory. This problem is closely related to machine learning and optimization, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of a recovery matrix to establish a relationship between observations and feature weights suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.RO (robotics) and cs.SY (systems and control). Finally, the application of the proposed algorithm to a simulated robot manipulator conducting free-space motions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.CV (computer vision), which often deals with the analysis of robot motion and manipulation.
